"65:8:11" : {s: 65, a: 8, w: 11, r: "شدد", t: "شَدِيدًۭا", l: "شَدِيد", lc: 56, tl: "shadīdan", lb: "কড়া",e: "severe", b: "কঠিন", i: "sangat/keras", f: 11, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
"65:8:12" : {s: 65, a: 8, w: 12, r: "عذب", t: "وَعَذَّبْنَٰهَا", l: "عَذَّبَ", lc: 41, tl: "waʿadhabnāhā", lb: "শাস্তি দেওয়া, আযাব দেওয়া",e: "and We punished it", b: "তাদেরকে শাস্তি দিয়েছিলাম", i: "dan Kami mengazabnya", f: 1, rm: "chastisement, castigate, punishment, torture, torment, retribution, abstain/desist (e.g. from eating due to excessive thirst), relinquish, quit. To deny a thing, hinder anyone from, be inaccessible, prevent."},
"65:8:13" : {s: 65, a: 8, w: 13, r: "عذب", t: "عَذَابًۭا", l: "عَذَاب", lc: 322, tl: "ʿadhāban", lb: "শাস্তি, আযাব, দুর্যোগ",e: "a punishment", b: "শাস্তি", i: "azab", f: 38, rm: "chastisement, castigate, punishment, torture, torment, retribution, abstain/desist (e.g. from eating due to excessive thirst), relinquish, quit. To deny a thing, hinder anyone from, be inaccessible, prevent."},
