"65:12:24" : {s: 65, a: 12, w: 24, r: "شيا", t: "شَىْءٍ", l: "شَىْء", lc: 283, tl: "shayin", lb: "কিছু, বস্তু, কোনো কিছু",e: "things", b: "কিছুর", i: "sesuatu", f: 179, rm: "to will/wish. shaiun (pl. ashyaaun) - thing/matter, affair in any way, at all, what is willed or wished, aught, any extent. In direct objective case it is often used to denote the meaning a little, bit, at all. Adverbially it means in any way, at all."},
